The `IsAugPath.augment_vertex_subset` lemma asserts that the set of vertices covered by the matching `M` is a subset of the vertices covered by the augmented matching `M ∆ E(P)`. The proof relies on the fact that any vertex `v` covered by `M` is either not in the path `P` (in which case its incident matching edge is preserved) or is an internal vertex of `P` (since endpoints of `P` are not covered by `M`). For an internal vertex `v`, which is incident to exactly two edges in `P`, the alternating property of `P` ensures that exactly one of these edges is in `M`. Consequently, the other edge is not in `M` and thus belongs to `M ∆ E(P)`, covering `v` in the new matching.

